name: androidpublisher
title: Google Play Developer API
description: Lets Android application developers access their Google Play accounts.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.desc: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

parameters.name: key
parameters.desc: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

parameters.name: oauth_token
parameters.desc: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

parameters.name: prettyPrint
parameters.desc: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

parameters.name: quotaUser
parameters.desc: Available to use for quota purposes for server-side applications. Can be any arbitrary string assigned to a user, but should not exceed 40 characters. Overrides userIp if both are provided.

parameters.name: userIp
parameters.desc: IP address of the site where the request originates. Use this if you want to enforce per-user limits.

fields.name: symbolType
fields.desc: The type of the deobfuscation file.

fields.name: defaultPrice
fields.desc: Default price cannot be zero and must be less than the full subscription price. Default price is always in the developer's Checkout merchant currency. Targeted countries have their prices set automatically based on the default_price.

fields.name: start
fields.desc: Defines the first day on which the price takes effect.

fields.name: developerComment
fields.desc: A comment from a developer.

fields.name: userComment
fields.desc: A comment from a user.

fields.name: authorName
fields.desc: The name of the user who wrote the review.

fields.name: comments
fields.desc: A repeated field containing comments for the review.

fields.name: reviewId
fields.desc: Unique identifier for this review.

fields.name: deferralInfo
fields.desc: The information about the new desired expiry time for the subscription.

schemas.name: SubscriptionPurchase
schemas.desc: A SubscriptionPurchase resource indicates the status of a user's subscription purchase.

fields.name: autoRenewing
fields.desc: Whether the subscription will automatically be renewed when it reaches its current expiry time.

fields.name: cancelReason
fields.desc:
The reason why a subscription was cancelled or is not auto-renewing. Possible values are:  
- User cancelled the subscription 
- Subscription was cancelled by the system, for example because of a billing problem

fields.name: expiryTimeMillis
fields.desc: Time at which the subscription will expire, in milliseconds since the Epoch.

fields.name: startTimeMillis
fields.desc: Time at which the subscription was granted, in milliseconds since the Epoch.

fields.name: priceCurrencyCode
fields.desc: ISO 4217 currency code for the subscription price. For example, if the price is specified in British pounds sterling, price_currency_code is "GBP".

fields.name: userCancellationTimeMillis
fields.desc: The time at which the subscription was canceled by the user, in milliseconds since the epoch. Only present if cancelReason is 0.

fields.name: countryCode
fields.desc: ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 billing country/region code of the user at the time the subscription was granted.

fields.name: developerPayload
fields.desc: A developer-specified string that contains supplemental information about an order.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This kind represents a subscriptionPurchase object in the androidpublisher service.

fields.name: paymentState
fields.desc:
The payment state of the subscription. Possible values are:  
- Payment pending 
- Payment received

fields.name: priceAmountMicros
fields.desc: Price of the subscription, not including tax. Price is expressed in micro-units, where 1,000,000 micro-units represents one unit of the currency. For example, if the subscription price is â‚¬1.99, price_amount_micros is 1990000.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "androidpublisher#tracksListResponse".

fields.name: defaultPrice
fields.desc: Default price cannot be zero. In-app products can never be free. Default price is always in the developer's Checkout merchant currency.

fields.name: listings
fields.desc: List of localized title and description data.

fields.name: prices
fields.desc: Prices per buyer region. None of these prices should be zero. In-app products can never be free.

fields.name: season
fields.desc: Definition of a season for a seasonal subscription. Can be defined only for yearly subscriptions.

fields.name: sku
fields.desc: The stock-keeping-unit (SKU) of the product, unique within an app.

fields.name: subscriptionPeriod
fields.desc: Subscription period, specified in ISO 8601 format. Acceptable values are "P1W" (one week), "P1M" (one month), "P3M" (three months), "P6M" (six months), and "P1Y" (one year).

fields.name: trialPeriod
fields.desc: Trial period, specified in ISO 8601 format. Acceptable values are anything between "P7D" (seven days) and "P999D" (999 days). Seasonal subscriptions cannot have a trial period.

fields.name: defaultLanguage
fields.desc: The default language of the localized data, as defined by BCP 47. e.g. "en-US", "en-GB".

fields.name: packageName
fields.desc: The package name of the parent app.

fields.name: purchaseType
fields.desc: Purchase type enum value. Unmodifiable after creation.

schemas.name: ApkBinary
schemas.desc: Represents the binary payload of an APK.

fields.name: sha1
fields.desc: A sha1 hash of the APK payload, encoded as a hex string and matching the output of the sha1sum command.

fields.name: externallyHostedApk
fields.desc: The definition of the externally-hosted APK and where it is located.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "androidpublisher#apksListResponse".

schemas.name: Entitlement
schemas.desc: An Entitlement resource indicates a user's current entitlement to an inapp item or subscription.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This kind represents an entitlement object in the androidpublisher service.

fields.name: productId
fields.desc: The SKU of the product.

fields.name: productType
fields.desc:
The type of the inapp product. Possible values are:  
- In-app item: "inapp" 
- Subscription: "subs"

fields.name: token
fields.desc: The token which can be verified using the subscriptions or products API.

fields.name: binary
fields.desc: Information about the binary payload of this APK.

fields.name: versionCode
fields.desc: The version code of the APK, as specified in the APK's manifest file.

fields.name: end
fields.desc: Inclusive end date of the recurrence period.

fields.name: prorations
fields.desc: Optionally present list of prorations for the season. Each proration is a one-off discounted entry into a subscription. Each proration contains the first date on which the discount is available and the new pricing information.

fields.name: start
fields.desc: Inclusive start date of the recurrence period.

fields.name: priceMicros
fields.desc: The price in millionths of the currency base unit represented as a string.

fields.name: currency
fields.desc: 3 letter Currency code, as defined by ISO 4217.

fields.name: nativePlatform
fields.desc: Comma separated list of native platforms (e.g. "arm", "arm7")

fields.name: screenDensityDpi
fields.desc: Screen density in DPI

fields.name: deviceClass
fields.desc: Device class (e.g. tablet)

fields.name: cpuModel
fields.desc: Device CPU model e.g. "MSM8974"

fields.name: glEsVersion
fields.desc: OpenGL version

fields.name: manufacturer
fields.desc: Device manufacturer (e.g. Motorola)

fields.name: productName
fields.desc: Device model name (e.g. Droid)

fields.name: ramMb
fields.desc: Device RAM in Megabytes e.g. "2048"

fields.name: screenHeightPx
fields.desc: Screen height in pixels

fields.name: screenWidthPx
fields.desc: Screen width in pixels

fields.name: cpuMake
fields.desc: Device CPU make e.g. "Qualcomm"

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "androidpublisher#inappproductsBatchResponse".

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "androidpublisher#inappproductsListResponse".

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "androidpublisher#listingsListResponse".

schemas.name: SubscriptionDeferralInfo
schemas.desc: A SubscriptionDeferralInfo contains the data needed to defer a subscription purchase to a future expiry time.

fields.name: desiredExpiryTimeMillis
fields.desc: The desired next expiry time to assign to the subscription, in milliseconds since the Epoch. The given time must be later/greater than the current expiry time for the subscription.

fields.name: expectedExpiryTimeMillis
fields.desc: The expected expiry time for the subscription. If the current expiry time for the subscription is not the value specified here, the deferral will not occur.

fields.name: day
fields.desc: Day of a month, value in [1, 31] range. Valid range depends on the specified month.

fields.name: month
fields.desc: Month of a year. e.g. 1 = JAN, 2 = FEB etc.

schemas.name: ProductPurchase
schemas.desc: A ProductPurchase resource indicates the status of a user's inapp product purchase.

fields.name: consumptionState
fields.desc:
The consumption state of the inapp product. Possible values are:  
- Yet to be consumed 
- Consumed

fields.name: developerPayload
fields.desc: A developer-specified string that contains supplemental information about an order.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This kind represents an inappPurchase object in the androidpublisher service.

fields.name: purchaseState
fields.desc:
The purchase state of the order. Possible values are:  
- Purchased 
- Cancelled

fields.name: purchaseTimeMillis
fields.desc: The time the product was purchased, in milliseconds since the epoch (Jan 1, 1970).

schemas.name: VoidedPurchase
schemas.desc: A VoidedPurchase resource indicates a purchase that was either cancelled/refunded/charged-back.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: This kind represents a voided purchase object in the androidpublisher service.

fields.name: purchaseTimeMillis
fields.desc: The time at which the purchase was made, in milliseconds since the epoch (Jan 1, 1970).

fields.name: purchaseToken
fields.desc: The token that was generated when a purchase was made. This uniquely identifies a purchase.

fields.name: voidedTimeMillis
fields.desc: The time at which the purchase was cancelled/refunded/charged-back, in milliseconds since the epoch (Jan 1, 1970).

schemas.name: AppEdit
schemas.desc: Represents an edit of an app. An edit allows clients to make multiple changes before committing them in one operation.

fields.name: expiryTimeSeconds
fields.desc: The time at which the edit will expire and will be no longer valid for use in any subsequent API calls (encoded as seconds since the Epoch).

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The ID of the edit that can be used in subsequent API calls.

fields.name: contactEmail
fields.desc: The user-visible support email for this app.

fields.name: contactPhone
fields.desc: The user-visible support telephone number for this app.

fields.name: contactWebsite
fields.desc: The user-visible website for this app.

fields.name: defaultLanguage
fields.desc: Default language code, in BCP 47 format (eg "en-US").

fields.name: language
fields.desc: The language code, in BCP 47 format (eg "en-US").

fields.name: recentChanges
fields.desc: Describe what's new in your APK.

fields.name: language
fields.desc: Language localization code (for example, "de-AT" for Austrian German).

fields.name: shortDescription
fields.desc: Short description of the app (previously known as promo text); this may be up to 80 characters in length.

fields.name: title
fields.desc: App's localized title.

fields.name: video
fields.desc: URL of a promotional YouTube video for the app.

fields.name: fullDescription
fields.desc: Full description of the app; this may be up to 4000 characters in length.

fields.name: lastModified
fields.desc: The last time at which this comment was updated.

fields.name: text
fields.desc: The content of the comment, i.e. reply body.

fields.name: fileSize
fields.desc: If set this field indicates that this APK has an Expansion File uploaded to it: this APK does not reference another APK's Expansion File. The field's value is the size of the uploaded Expansion File in bytes.

fields.name: referencesVersion
fields.desc: If set this APK's Expansion File references another APK's Expansion File. The file_size field will not be set.

fields.name: lastEdited
fields.desc: The time at which the reply took effect.

fields.name: replyText
fields.desc: The reply text that was applied.

fields.name: deviceMetadata
fields.desc: Some information about the characteristics of the user's device

fields.name: starRating
fields.desc: The star rating associated with the review, from 1 to 5.

fields.name: text
fields.desc: The content of the comment, i.e. review body. In some cases users have been able to write a review with separate title and body; in those cases the title and body are concatenated and separated by a tab character.

fields.name: thumbsDownCount
fields.desc: Number of users who have given this review a thumbs down

fields.name: thumbsUpCount
fields.desc: Number of users who have given this review a thumbs up

fields.name: androidOsVersion
fields.desc: Integer Android SDK version of the user's device at the time the review was written, e.g. 23 is Marshmallow. May be absent.

fields.name: appVersionCode
fields.desc: Integer version code of the app as installed at the time the review was written. May be absent.

fields.name: appVersionName
fields.desc: String version name of the app as installed at the time the review was written. May be absent.

fields.name: device
fields.desc: Codename for the reviewer's device, e.g. klte, flounder. May be absent.

fields.name: lastModified
fields.desc: The last time at which this comment was updated.

fields.name: originalText
fields.desc: Untranslated text of the review, in the case where the review has been translated. If the review has not been translated this is left blank.

fields.name: reviewerLanguage
fields.desc: Language code for the reviewer. This is taken from the device settings so is not guaranteed to match the language the review is written in. May be absent.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "androidpublisher#apkListingsListResponse".

fields.name: id
fields.desc: A unique id representing this image.

fields.name: sha1
fields.desc: A sha1 hash of the image that was uploaded.

fields.name: url
fields.desc: A URL that will serve a preview of the image.

fields.name: replyText
fields.desc: The text to set as the reply. Replies of more than approximately 350 characters will be rejected. HTML tags will be stripped.

fields.name: newExpiryTimeMillis
fields.desc: The new expiry time for the subscription in milliseconds since the Epoch.

schemas.name: ExternallyHostedApk
schemas.desc: Defines an APK available for this application that is hosted externally and not uploaded to Google Play. This function is only available to enterprises who are using Google Play for Work, and whos application is restricted to the enterprise private channel

fields.name: iconBase64
fields.desc: The icon image from the APK, as a base64 encoded byte array.

fields.name: packageName
fields.desc: The package name.

fields.name: fileSha1Base64
fields.desc: The SHA1 checksum of this APK, represented as a base64 encoded byte array.

fields.name: fileSize
fields.desc: The file size in bytes of this APK.

fields.name: maximumSdk
fields.desc: The maximum SDK supported by this APK (optional).

fields.name: minimumSdk
fields.desc: The minimum SDK targeted by this APK.

fields.name: usesFeatures
fields.desc: The features required by this APK (optional).

fields.name: applicationLabel
fields.desc: The application label.

fields.name: certificateBase64s
fields.desc: A certificate (or array of certificates if a certificate-chain is used) used to signed this APK, represented as a base64 encoded byte array.

fields.name: versionName
fields.desc: The version name of this APK.

fields.name: fileSha256Base64
fields.desc: The SHA256 checksum of this APK, represented as a base64 encoded byte array.

fields.name: versionCode
fields.desc: The version code of this APK.

fields.name: usesPermissions
fields.desc: The permissions requested by this APK.

fields.name: externallyHostedUrl
fields.desc: The URL at which the APK is hosted. This must be an https URL.

fields.name: nativeCodes
fields.desc: The native code environments supported by this APK (optional).

fields.name: externallyHostedApk
fields.desc: The definition of the externally-hosted APK and where it is located.

schemas.name: ExternallyHostedApkUsesPermission
schemas.desc: A permission used by this APK.

fields.name: maxSdkVersion
fields.desc: Optionally, the maximum SDK version for which the permission is required.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name of the permission requested.

optinalQueryParams.name: startTime
optinalQueryParams.desc: The time, in milliseconds since the Epoch, of the oldest voided in-app product purchase that you want to see in the response. The value of this parameter cannot be older than 30 days and is ignored if a pagination token is set. Default value is current time minus 30 days.

optinalQueryParams.name: endTime
optinalQueryParams.desc: The time, in milliseconds since the Epoch, of the newest voided in-app product purchase that you want to see in the response. The value of this parameter cannot be greater than the current time and is ignored if a pagination token is set. Default value is current time.
